---
import MainLayout from '../../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
---

<MainLayout
  title="Blog — DoItSwift"
  description="Guides and practical tips on image formats, privacy, and getting the most out of DoItSwift tools."
  keywords="doitswift blog, image converter tips, heic webp guides"
>
  <section class="content-page">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Blog</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        We are preparing articles and short guides on image formats, compression, and privacy-minded workflows. New
        posts will appear here first — no newsletter required.
      </p>
      <p>
        In the meantime, our <a href="/image/" class="link-back">image tools hub</a> and the <a href="/" class="link-back">home page</a> include on-page help and FAQs to
        get you unstuck quickly.
      </p>

      <h2>Topics we are writing about</h2>
      <div class="topic-grid">
        <div class="topic-card">
          <h3>HEIC &amp; iPhone photos</h3>
          <p>Opening HEIC on Windows, when to convert to JPG, and quality tradeoffs for sharing online.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="topic-card">
          <h3>WebP &amp; AVIF</h3>
          <p>Modern formats for the web, browser support, and when JPG is still the right choice.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="topic-card">
          <h3>Privacy-first workflows</h3>
          <p>Why local processing matters, and how to verify that tools are not uploading your files.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="topic-card">
          <h3>Icons &amp; favicons</h3>
          <p>Creating crisp favicons and understanding ICO sizes for different browsers and devices.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="section-tail">
        <a href="/image/" class="link-back">Browse image tools →</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</MainLayout>
